owens president and ceo products petrochemical petroleum fuel lubricants revenue us  billion  net income us  billion  total assets us  billion  number of employees   website sunocoinccom sunoco service station ypsilanti michigan sunoco is an american petroleum and petrochemical manufacturer headquartered in newtown square pennsylvania united states formerly known as sun company inc – and – and sun oil co – sunoco is one of the largest gasoline distribution companies in the united states with sunoco brand gasoline being sold in over  outlets spanning  states just over a third hosting convenience stores since  sunoco has been a wholly owned subsidiary of energy transfer partners based in dallas texas in  it was ranked as the third largest company by revenue in pennsylvania after amerisourcebergen and comcast in  the company decided to exit the oil refinery business in canada the sunoco brand was licensed for the ontario retail gas station operations of suncor energy until  following suncors acquisition of petrocanada all canadian sunoco outlets were converted to petrocanada branding in  it was announced that  sunoco convenience stores would be sold to seven  i holdings co parent company of eleven for  billion also as a part of the deal sunoco also said they would be supplying  billion gallons of fuel annually for  years to eleven convenience stores contents  history  s to s founding and growth  custom blending  s to s acquisitions and branding  exit from refinery business  joint venture with carlyle group  sale to energy transfer partners and merger with susser holdings  exclusive deals  sale of stores to seven  i holdings co  environmental record  as a sponsor  see also  references  external links historyedit s to s founding and growthedit the integrated oil company now known as sunoco began as the peoples natural gas company in pittsburgh pennsylvania in  its partners – joseph newton pew philip pisano and edward o emerson – decided to expand their gas business with a stake in the new oil discoveries in ohio and pennsylvania four years later the growing enterprise became the sun oil company of ohio sun oil diversified quickly active in production and distribution of oil as well as processing and marketing refined products by  the company was incorporated in new jersey as sun company and turned its interest to the new spindletop field in texas pews sons j howard pew and joseph n pew jr would take over the company after their fathers death newspaper ad for sunoco motor oil then known as sun oil tulsa daily world november   with a growing portfolio of oil fields and refineries in hand sun opened its first service station in ardmore pennsylvania in  the name changed back to sun oil company in  and in  sun became a publicly traded company on the new york stock exchange sunoco ranked th among united states corporations in the value of world war ii production contracts sun expanded internationally following the war its first canadian refinery was built in  in sarnia ontario home to a burgeoning new petrochemical industry sun established a facility at venezuelas lake maracaibo in  which produced over a billion barrels  m before the operation was nationalized in  custom blendingedit sunoco is perhaps best known to consumers for its custom blending pumps an innovation that beginning in  allowed customers of sunoco service stations to choose from several octane grades through a single pumpcitation needed sunoco stations offered as many as eight grades of custom blended gasolines from its dial a grade pumps ranging from subregular sunoco  to sunoco citation needed the latter a superpremium grade of  octanecitation needed that was advertised as the highest octane pump gascitation needed and very popular with operators of vpowered muscle cars of the scitation needed s to s acquisitions and brandingedit in  sun established its great canadian oil sands limited facility in northern alberta canada to help unlock the estimated  billion barrels  km of recoverable oil in the athabasca oil sands in  sun oil merged with tulsa oklahomabased sunray dx oil company which refined and marketed gasoline under the dx brand in several midwestern states and included several refineries including one in tulsa that was operated by sun until its sale in june  to holly corporation of dallas this move expanded suns marketing area into the midcontinent region sun oil continued marketing its petroleum products under both the sunoco and dx brands through the s and into the s in the late s sun began rebranding dx stations in the midwest to the sunoco brand and even introduced the highoctane sunoco ultra  gasoline to stations in that region but by the early s they pulled out of virtually all areas in the southeastern us and west of the mississippi resulting in the closing and rebranding of service stations and jobbers to other brands in those areas notably sinclair in oklahoma with increased diversification sun oil company was renamed sun company in  in  sun acquired the us oil and gas properties of texas pacific oil company inc a subsidiary of the seagram company ltd for us billion—the second largest acquisition in us history to that date through the s sun developed oil interests in the north sea and offshore china and expanded its holdings in both oil and coal with additional us business acquisitions in  consumers saw the arrival of sunoco ultra  the markets highest octane unleaded gasoline then in  sun undertook a major restructuring to segregate its domestic oil and gas exploration and production business and the focus the company on its refining and marketing business this led to the acquisition of atlantic refining and marketing and in effect that companys convenience store chain aplus including its philadelphia refinery which was later merged with the former gulf oil refinery next door that sunoco acquired from chevron by the s sun had departed the international exploration business and was fully dedicated to its branded products and services in  sunoco acquired the philadelphia chevron oil refinery consolidating operations with its own adjacent which it had acquired with atlantic sun sold its remaining interest in canadas suncor energy in  but markets product from two refineries – one in toledo ohio and the other sarnia ontario – in joint ventures in  sun company inc became sunoco inc in  the toledo facility was sold to pbf energy by  sun had acquired allied signal inc chemical plants allied signal inc being on the stock exchange sold half of the company to honeywell inc and the other half to sunoco inc the chemical portion of the business was called sunoco chemicals inc in  the speedway superamerica chain of gas stations and convenience stores exited the southeastern united states and sold most of their operations to sunoco shortly prior to this sunoco acquired many service stations from coastal petroleum especially its stations in florida this has led to the reintroduction of the sunoco brand to areas it pulled out of ten years earlier coincidentally speedway would later reenter the southeast with its purchase of hess corporations downstream operations in  mirroring that of sunocos return to the southeast sunoco fuel supply truck at  nascar race in  sunoco replaced conocophillips  brand as the official fuel of nascar after conocophillips abandoned the marketing of the mobil brand name in the washington dc area sunoco purchased these rights and has since been converting maryland and virginia mobil stations to the sunoco brand bringing the aplus convenience store with them – prior to this these stations had convenience stores under the circle k or on the run brands in september  sunoco announced the sale of its retail heating oil and propane distribution business to superior plus corp for  million in cash in october  sunoco announced it will idle and possibly permanently shut down its eagle pointwestville nj plant laying off over  employees exit from refinery businessedit in december  sunoco sold its refinery in toledo ohio to pbf energy for us effective  september  sunoco announced that it would exit the crude oil refining business and seek to sell its philadelphia and marcus hook refineries by mid the company has said that its cost for exiting the refining business could be as high as us billion according to one report the company had lost some us on refining operations since  an earlier report provided a figure of us on december   sunoco announced it would accelerate closure of the marcus hook facility with a target completion in  days the marcus hook facility founded in  and covering  acres was dedicated exclusively to the processing of light sweet crude oil this processing focus combined with volatility in crude oil prices are considered contributing factors to both this refinerys closure and sunocos exit from the refinery business joint venture with carlyle groupedit after weeks of negotiations it was announced that sunoco would be forming a joint venture with the carlyle group allowing for the continuation of operations at the philadelphia refinery and saving over  jobs the joint venture began in late  sale to energy transfer partners and merger with susser holdingsedit in  dallasbased energy company energy transfer partners purchased sunoco making sunoco a wholly owned subsidiary as energy transfer partners was more interested in sunocos pipeline and refining business that the company was originally planning on exiting it led to speculation that energy transfer partners would eventually spinoff sunocos retail business or sell it outright to a competitor in  energy transfer partners announced its purchase of susser holdings corporation the parent company of stripes convenience stores and plans on merging it into sunoco upon completion of the merger sunoco will be placed into a limited partnership called susser petroleum partners lp in which energy transfer will have an ownership stake the deal saw the arrival of the sunoco brand in texas 