  the company was incorporated in new jersey as sun company and turned its interest to the new spindletop field in texas pews sons j howard pew and joseph n pew jr would take over the company after their fathers death newspaper ad for sunoco motor oil then known as sun oil tulsa daily world november   with a growing portfolio of oil fields and refineries in hand sun opened its first service station in ardmore pennsylvania in  the name changed back to sun oil company in  and in  sun became a publicly traded company on the new york stock exchange sunoco ranked th among united states corporations in the value of world war ii production contracts sun expanded internationally following the war its first canadian refinery was built in  in sarnia ontario home to a burgeoning new petrochemical industry sun established a facility at venezuelas lake maracaibo in  which produced over a billion barrels  m before the operation was nationalized in  custom blendingedit sunoco is perhaps best known to consumers for its custom blending pumps an innovation that beginning in  allowed customers of sunoco service stations to choose from several octane grades through a single pumpcitation needed sunoco stations offered as many as eight grades of custom blended gasolines from its dial a grade pumps ranging from subregular sunoco  to sunoco citation needed the latter a superpremium grade of  octanecitation needed that was advertised as the highest octane pump gascitation needed and very popular with operators of vpowered muscle cars of the scitation needed s to s acquisitions and brandingedit in  sun established its great canadian oil sands limited facility in northern alberta canada to help unlock the estimated  billion barrels  km of recoverable oil in the athabasca oil sands in  sun oil merged with tulsa oklahomabased sunray dx oil company which refined and marketed gasoline under the dx brand in several midwestern states and included several refineries including one in tulsa that was operated by sun until its sale in june  to holly corporation of dallas this move expanded suns marketing area into the midcontinent region sun oil continued marketing its petroleum products under both the sunoco and dx brands through the s and into the s in the late s sun began rebranding dx stations in the midwest to the sunoco brand and even introduced the highoctane sunoco ultra  gasoline to stations in that region but by the early s they pulled out of virtually all areas in the southeastern us and west of the mississippi resulting in the closing and rebranding of service stations and jobbers to other brands in those areas notably sinclair in oklahoma with increased diversification sun oil company was renamed sun company in  in  sun acquired the us oil and gas properties of texas pacific oil company inc a subsidiary of the seagram company ltd for us billion—the second largest acquisition in us history to that date through the s sun developed oil interests in the north sea and offshore china and expanded its holdings in both oil and coal with additional us business acquisitions in  consumers saw the arrival of sunoco ultra  the markets highest octane unleaded gasoline then in  sun undertook a major restructuring to segregate its domestic oil and gas exploration and production business and the focus the company on its refining and marketing business this led to the acquisition of atlantic refining and marketing and in effect that companys convenience store chain aplus including its philadelphia refinery which was later merged with the former gulf oil refinery next door that sunoco acquired from chevron by the s sun had departed the international exploration business and was fully dedicated to its branded products and services in  sunoco acquired the philadelphia chevron oil refinery consolidating operations with its own adjacent which it had acquired with atlantic sun sold its remaining interest in canadas suncor energy in  but markets product from two refineries – one in toledo ohio and the other sarnia ontario – in joint ventures in  sun company inc became sunoco inc in  the toledo facility was sold to pbf energy by  sun had acquired allied signal inc chemical plants allied signal inc being on the stock exchange sold half of the company to honeywell inc and the other half to sunoco inc the chemical portion of the business was called sunoco chemicals inc in  the speedway superamerica chain of gas stations and convenience stores exited the southeastern united states and sold most of their operations to sunoco shortly prior to this sunoco acquired many service stations from coastal petroleum especially its stations in florida this has led to the reintroduction of the sunoco brand to areas it pulled out of ten years earlier coincidentally speedway would later reenter the southeast with its purchase of hess corporations downstream operations in  mirroring that of sunocos return to the southeast sunoco fuel supply truck at  nascar race in  sunoco replaced conocophillips  brand as the official fuel of nascar after conocophillips abandoned the marketing of the mobil brand name in the washington dc area sunoco purchased these rights and has since been converting maryland and virginia mobil stations to the sunoco brand bringing the aplus convenience store with them – prior to this these stations had convenience stores under the circle k or on the run brands in september  sunoco announced the sale of its retail heating oil and propane distribution business to superior plus corp for  million in cash in october  sunoco announced it will idle and possibly permanently shut down its eagle pointwestville nj plant laying off over  employees exit from refinery businessedit in december  sunoco sold its refinery in toledo ohio to pbf energy for us effective  september  sunoco announced that it would exit the crude oil refining business and seek to sell its philadelphia and marcus hook refineries by mid the company has said that its cost for exiting the refining business could be as high as us billion according to one report the company had lost some us on refining operations since  an earlier report provided a figure of us on december   sunoco announced it would accelerate closure of the marcus hook facility with a target completion in  days the marcus hook facility founded in  and covering  acres was dedicated exclusively to the processing of light sweet crude oil this processing focus combined with volatility in crude oil prices are considered contributing factors to both this refinerys closure and sunocos exit from the refinery business joint venture with carlyle groupedit after weeks of negotiations it was announced that sunoco would be forming a joint venture with the carlyle group allowing for the continuation of operations at the philadelphia refinery and saving over  jobs the joint venture began in late  sale to energy transfer partners and merger with susser holdingsedit in  dallasbased energy company energy transfer partners purchased sunoco making sunoco a wholly owned subsidiary as energy transfer partners was more interested in sunocos pipeline and refining business that the company was originally planning on exiting it led to speculation that energy transfer partners would eventually spinoff sunocos retail business or sell it outright to a competitor in  energy transfer partners announced its purchase of susser holdings corporation the parent company of stripes convenience stores and plans on merging it into sunoco upon completion of the merger sunoco will be placed into a limited partnership called susser petroleum partners lp in which energy transfer will have an ownership stake the deal saw the arrival of the sunoco brand in texas where it replaced valero at the stripes locations stripes and aplus remain separate brands also in  sunoco acquired aloha petroleum in  sunoco entered into an agreement to purchase md america operations in east texas that same year sunoco became a subway franchisee by opening subway at the north midway service plaza on the pennsylvania turnpike near bedford pennsylvania exclusive dealsedit in addition to their sponsorship deal with nascar sunoco also has exclusive deals as the gasoline supplier at the travel plazas along the ohio turnpike pennsylvania turnpike new jersey turnpike garden state parkway atlantic city expressway palisades parkway and delaware turnpike sunoco also operates some of the filling stations on the new york thruway as well as the two service areas  chesapeake house and maryland house  along interstate  in maryland in addition sunoco also owns  operates a station with an aplus convenience store at pittsburgh international airport as sunoco has a very large market share in pittsburgh due to its large presence in western pennsylvania sunoco is a longtime sponsor of the pittsburgh pirates with an advertisement for sunoco being present in left field at pnc park sunoco became the official current fuel supplier of the izod indycar series now the verizon indycar series in mid sale of stores to seven  i holdings coedit on april   sunoco announced it would sell  convenience stores to seven  i holdings co parent company of eleven as well as supply  billion gallons of fuel to eleven convenience stores annually for  years the company also announced they would be selling  more stores to seven  i by the end of q  environmental recordedit sunoco was the only oil company to initially sign the coalition for environmentally responsible economies ceres principal however as of march  sunoco is not listed as a ceres coalition or company network member of ceres in  sunoco leaked  gallons of oil into the john heinz wildlife refuge in pennsylvania through a cracked pipe sunocos safety systems did not detect the leak which was reported by a hiker in the wildlife refuge pennsylvania senator john heinz for whom the john heinz national wildlife refuge is named was killed on april   when a sun company helicopter collided with an airplane carrying the senator sun company is the predecessor of sunoco that accident also killed two children at the merion elementary school playground into which debris from the two aircraft fell after the collision the national transportation safety board determined that the probable cause of the accident included poor judgment on the part of the captain of the sun company helicopter and his failure to maintain safe separation from the senator’s airplane as of march  records maintained by the united states pipeline and hazardous materials safety administration phmsa show that sunoco has experienced  hazardous liquids incidents since  phmsa defines an incident as an event that involves a release of gas from a pipeline or of liquefied natural gas or gas from an lng facility that results in a death or injury necessitating hospitalization or property damage of  or more these  incidents resulted in  of property damage in terms of number of incidents sunoco has the worst safety record of  active pipeline operators who report operating data to phmsa in  sunoco along with other defendants was sued by the commonwealth of pennsylvania which alleged that sunoco and the other defendants polluted the waters of the commonwealth with mtbe a gasoline additive the commonwealth also alleged that the defendants including sunoco improperly accepted state funding to clean up spills which occurred prior to  and which were therefore not covered by the fund as a sponsoredit sunoco was penske racings sponsor of choice for many years particularly in the scca transam series where roger penskes sunoco camaros won the championship in  and  sunoco also sponsored penske porsches in the scca canam series and won the indianapolis  in  with penske and driver mark donohue in  nascar team owner billy hagan acquired sponsorship from sunoco for four seasons sterling marlin drove the  sunoco ultra oldsmobile during the  seasons and terry labonte for the  seasons in  sunoco became the official fuel of the nhra in  as part of the daytona update coinciding with the  daytona  a nascar version of the toyota camry with sunoco as its main sponsor appears in real racing  see alsoedit philadelphia portal companies portal  philadelphia refinery fire refinery at the time was owned by gulf oil referencesedit  a b c d osullivan sean  dec  sunoco to close refinery the news journal retrieved  dec    a b  annual report sunoco retrieved    retail marketing  overview archived march   at the wayback machine  csnews exclusive top chains continue store growth through acquisition despite market turmoilpermanent dead link  cable news network fortune   states pennsylvania companies archived october   at the wayback machine cnn money retrieved on   a b c d e nixon alex  sep  sunoco refineries could be closed pittsburgh tribunereview triblive business retrieved  sep    a b sunoco to sell  us stores to eleven operator for  billion reuters  retrieved    peck merton j  scherer frederic m the weapons acquisition process an economic analysis  harvard business school p     sunoco chemicals and the sarnia refinery sunocochemcom retrieved    speedway to acquire hess retail marathon petroleum corporation retrieved  may    sunoco to sell retail heating oil business reuters september  permanent dead link  key peter  jan  how the oil refining industry is like a casino philadelphia business journal bizjournalscom retrieved  jan    the carlyle group and sunoco agree to form philadelphia refinery joint venture archived september   at the wayback machine  energy transfer partners buys oil refiner sunoco archived march   at the wayback machine usa today   a b c maykuth andrew sunoco parent buys texas chain for  billion phillycom retrieved  may    aloha saying goodbye to hawaii csp daily news retrieved    sunoco to fuel ohio turnpike archived march   at the wayback machine  service plazas  contact information pennsylvania turnpike commission retrieved august     sunoco drives onto njs garden state parkway a